For debugging client-side JavaScript, some things you can try for size in Firebug:<p>- Breakpoints in Firebug script debugger<p>- Find state of variables by assigning them to global vars temporarily, e.g.:<p>var debugState; // Delete me once you've finished debugging<p>function someFunction() {
  var state = 'interesting value I want to inspect';
  .... do some work on 'state'
  debugState = state;
}<p>Then access debugState in the Firebug console. The console allows you to use JavaScript to interact with your page.<p>- Using console.log(msg, ...) in your scripts. You can pass multiple variables and these will all get output to the console, e.g.:<p>console.log('The Carousel:', carousel, 'Foo:', bar, ...)
